 the services provided by the network. They analize the Availavility of the \'Core Telefónica Spanish Network\' under their proposed MLSBR strategy. The work showed the higher availability of this mechanism in comparison with the current dual-plane protection scheme. The analytical study is done using Markov’s chain model where the node reachability status is defined accordingly.','journal'),(251,'Mitigation of cascading failures on complex networks','Springer','not-in-selection',2012,'','','journal'),(252,'Mitigation of malicious attacks on networks','NAS','not-in-selection',2011,'','','journal'),(253,'Mitigation strategies on scale-free networks against cascading failures','ScienceDirect','not-in-selection',2013,'','','journal'),(254,'Model for cascading failures in complex networks','APS','not-in-selection',2004,'','','journal'),(255,'Modeling cascading failures in the North American power grid','Springer','not-in-selection',2005,'','','journal'),(256,'Modeling interdependencies between the electricity and information infrastructures','Springer','not-in-selection',2007,'','','proceedings'),(257,'Modeling the dynamical interaction between epidemics on overlay networks','APS','not-in-selection',2011,'','','journal'),(258,'Modeling the Interaction of Power Line and SCADA Networks','IEEE','6754620',2014,'In this work, we discuss the robustness of a power line network and a SCADA network to interacting failures. Previous research on network robustness is mainly focused on the structural properties of a single network. However if systems consist of multiple interdependent networks, their interaction must be considered. This work considers power distribution systems which consist of a power line network and a SCADA network and evaluates the effects of the interaction between the two networks on the robustness of the systems. The evaluation results suggest that the robustness increases as the inter-similarity between the two networks increases.','The paper focuses on the